<h2>Monitter Twitter Widget</h2> 
It was inevitable that Twitter was going to be a success. Besides the social aspect since the failure of Google to provide a means for people to vote on links and the inevitable spam and SEO industries, people found in Twitter a quick means of sharing their web finds, their blog post opinions and the like. 

It is fairly easy to create a plugin using jQuery [monitter](http://monitter.com) provides one to do so. You just link to a file, edit your css and presto. It is also a good way to set up your own twitter monitor on a local host.

 
